  "result": "[Card(1764731543071, nid=1764731543071, due=47, ivl=0, queue=0)]"
}


{
  "id": "toolu_01BBTUkQNTZfCgU2ehbFxDAU",
  "call": {
    "function": "find_card_ids",
    "arguments": {
      "query": "*"
    }
  },
  "result": "[1764731543071]"
}

All three work! Here’s the comparison:



Function
Returns




find_note_ids("*")
[1764731543071] — just the note ID


find_note_ids gives just IDs (lightweight)



find_cards("*")
Card(1764731543071, nid=1764731543071, due=47, ivl=0, queue=0) — full Card object with scheduling info


find_card_ids("*")
[1764731543071] — just the card ID



Interesting that in this case the note ID and card ID happen to be the same (1764731543071). That’s because with a Basic note type, there’s exactly one card per note.
That just leaves sync — want me to try that too?
Sure. Delete that note, then sync.


